        "desc": "A large rectangular cavern, excavated with utmost skill and precision, extends\nfifty by sixty feet in the underground beneath the Blue Mountains. Straight\nwalls of hard trusty rock form the solid base for a high wooden ceiling fifteen\nfeet above. Arranged along the walls are many tables, cabinets and boards for\ntools, and in the centre of the room is a large anvil. Metal buckets, some\nfilled with scrap metal and some with iron-ore, stand by a door in the eastern\nwall ready to be emptied into the hot fire.\n",
