        "desc": "A circular cavern of dwarven make extends its arching walls inwards forming a\nspherical ceiling around an anvil in the centre of the cavern. The afferent\nwalls surround what appears to be a dwarven workshop. Broad shelves and large\nwooden cabinets precisely ordered on the walls and in clusters on the floor\nprovide storage space for many strange tools that are used by the dwarven\nmetal-workers. Despite the obvious completeness of the workshop it has not been\nused for a long time, as is apparent from the dust and cobwebs that span the\nroom.\n",
